\[
\frac{d^2v_y}{dt^2} = -\omega \frac{dv_x}{dt} = -\omega^2 v_y
\]
or
\[
\frac{d^2v_y}{dt^2} + \omega^2 v_y = 0 \tag{6}
\]

With the initial conditions \( v_x = v_y = 0 \) at \( t = 0 \), equation (6) has the solution:
\[
v_y = A \sin \omega t \tag{7}
\]
where \( A = \text{constant} \).

Thus,
\[
\frac{dv_y}{dt} = A \omega \cos \omega t = \omega \gamma - \omega v_x
\]

At \( t = 0 \), \( v_x = 0 \), hence:
