The magnetic fields in the upper branch and lower branch act in opposite directions. The current in the upper branch is $\frac{4I}{5}$ and in the lower branch is $\frac{I}{5}$. As the current is flowing through semicircles, the magnetic fields are given by:

\[
B_1 = \frac{\mu_0}{4a} \left(\frac{4I}{5}\right) = \frac{\mu_0 I}{5a}
\]

\[
B_2 = \frac{\mu_0}{4a} \left(\frac{I}{5}\right) = \frac{\mu_0 I}{20a}
\]

The net magnetic field is:

\[
B = B_1 - B_2 = \frac{3\mu_0 I}{20a}
\]

\end{document}
```

